This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it proposes a model for learning visually grounded representations of language. Additionally, the use of Gated Recurrent Unit networks and shared word embeddings are common techniques in natural language processing. 

The paper also involves visual input, which suggests it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The use of a multi-task objective and the focus on learning representations suggests that the paper could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper's focus on acquiring meaning representations for individual words and effectively using sequential structure in semantic interpretation suggests it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper's use of textual descriptions and visual representations suggests it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which often involves processing and analyzing text and images.
